race.description: Breeders Cup Juvenile Turf Sprint Stakes (G1)
race.comment: The first of the Breeders' Cup races now and it's a cracker to get things started. TRUE LOVE (9) looks to have plenty of class, winning comfortably at Newmarket last start over 1207m. Back to the shorter journey today, though she dominated a G2 over this trip back in June. Ticks plenty of boxes and looks the one to beat. SCHWARZENEGGER (11) looks the best of the US hopes following an impressive win as favourite in the Indian Summer last time out. Gate 11 is a niggle, but he showed good speed and strength last start and can continue to raise the bar. CY FAIR (10) missed narrowly two back before bolting in up at Woodbine most recently in the Algonquin as the race favourite. Can let the race unfold in front of her and with plenty of upside, she can storm over the top of them late. HAVANA ANNA (8) just missed behind TRUE LOVE last start and that form looks the line to follow. Has to be included on the back of that effort. BRUSSELS (1) looks to get a gun run along the rail and has claims.
